CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Baltimore City – Alcoholic Beverages – 46th Alcoholic Beverages District
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the Board of License Commissioners for Baltimore City to
4 issue a Class 7 micro–brewery license to the holder of a Class B–D–7 license in the
5 46th alcoholic beverages district, subject to a certain limitation; requiring the Board
6 to establish a standard template for certain memoranda of understanding by a certain
7 date; authorizing the Board of License Commissioners for Baltimore City to
8 authorize the transfer of a Class B–D–7 license from an area in the 40th alcoholic
9 beverages district into the 46th alcoholic beverages district; authorizing certain
10 holders of certain Class D licenses in the 46th alcoholic beverages district to apply for
11 a 7–day sales privilege under certain circumstances; requiring the Board to adopt
12 regulations establishing certain tiered penalties for license violations; authorizing a
13 license holder in a certain area in the 46th alcoholic beverages district to keep and
14 allow individuals to consume alcohol donated by a manufacturer or wholesaler under
15 certain circumstances; extending for a certain amount of time the expiration of an
